        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 12:43PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1243 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Milford to near Novi to near Romulus.
Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Warren, Troy, Southfield, Pontiac, Novi, Milford, Holly, Oxford,
Sterling Heights, Royal Oak, Birmingham, Rochester, Northville,
Ortonville, Detroit Zoo, Clarkston, West Bloomfield, Farmington
Hills, Rochester Hills, and Madison Heights.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
